==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[grove]] of small growth; a [[thicket]] of [[brushwood]]; a [[wood]] cut at certain times for [[fuel]] or other purposes, typically managed to promote growth and ensure a reliable supply of [[timber]]. See [[copse]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1957''': It was also enacted that all coppices or underwoods should be enclosed for periods of from four to seven years after felling. &mdash; H.R. Schubert, ''History of the British Iron and Steel Industry'', p. 216.

